00019  * Secure Hash Standard
00020  * proposed NIST SHS
00021  * coded for byte strings: number of bits is a multiple of 8

00028 /*
00029  * unsigned long qshs(char *s, int n);
00030  *
00031  * input:  
00032  *                s character array to be hashed
00033  *                n length of s in BYTES
00034  * output:
00035  *                return value: address of 5 unsigned longs holding hash
00036  *
00037  * machine dependencies:
00038  *                assumes a char is 8 bits
00039  */
00040 
00041 /*
00042  * passes test on:
00043  *                gauss (vax)
00044  *                3k (cray)
00045  *                slepian (MIPS)
00046  *                bird (sparcstation II)
00047  */

00053 static long nbits;
00054 static unsigned long *h;
00055 static unsigned long *w;
00056 static void shs1();
00057 /*
00058 static void packl (unsigned long);
00059 static void pack (unsigned char, unsigned char, unsigned char, unsigned char);
00060 static void shs1(void);
00061 static void opack(unsigned char);

00064 #define MASK        (unsigned long)0xffffffffL        /* in case more than 32 bits per long */
00065 
00066 /*
00067  * stick one byte into the current block; process the block when full
00068  */
00069 static void opack(c)
00070   unsigned char c;
00071 {
00072         int n32, nd32, shiftbits;
00073         register unsigned long x, mask, y;
00074         
00075         nd32 = (int)(nbits >> 5);  /* nbits/32 */
00076         n32 = (int)(nbits & 0x1f); /* nbits%32 */
00077         shiftbits = 24-n32;
00078         
00079         x = (unsigned long)(c<<shiftbits);
00080         mask = (unsigned long)(0xff << shiftbits);
00081         mask = ~mask;
00082         
00083         y = w[nd32];
00084         y = (y & mask) + x;
00085         w[nd32] = y;
00086         
00087         nbits += 8;
00088         if(nbits==512){
00089                 nbits = 0;
00090                 shs1();
00091         }
00092 }
00093 
00094 static void pack(c0, c1, c2, c3)
00095   unsigned char c0, c1, c2, c3;
00096 {
00097         int nd32;
00098         
00099         nd32 = (int)(nbits >> 5);
00100         w[nd32] = (u_long)(((u_long)c0<<24) | ((u_long)c1<<16) | ((u_long)c2<<8) | (u_long)c3);
00101         
00102         nbits += 32;
00103         if(nbits==512){
00104                 nbits = 0;
00105                 shs1();
00106         }
00107 }

00109 /*
00110  * stick a 4 byte number into the current block
00111  */
00112 static void
00113 packl(x)
00114   unsigned long x;
00115 {
00116         pack((unsigned char)(x>>24), (unsigned char)(x>>16),
00117              (unsigned char)(x>>8), (unsigned char)(x>>0));
00118 }

00120 /*
00121  * process one block
00122  */
00123 static void
00124 shs1()
00125 {
00126         unsigned long *wp;
00127         unsigned long temp;
00128         unsigned long A, B, C, D, E;
00129         int t;
00130         
00131 #define S(n,x) (u_long)(((x)<<(n))|((MASK&(x))>>(32-(n))))
00132         
00133         wp = w;
00134         t = 8;
00135         do {
00136                 wp[16] = S(1, (u_long)(wp[13]^wp[8]^wp[2]^wp[0]));
00137                 wp[17] = S(1, (u_long)(wp[14]^wp[9]^wp[3]^wp[1]));
00138                 wp[18] = S(1, (u_long)(wp[15]^wp[10]^wp[4]^wp[2]));
00139                 wp[19] = S(1, (u_long)(wp[16]^wp[11]^wp[5]^wp[3]));
00140                 wp[20] = S(1, (u_long)(wp[17]^wp[12]^wp[6]^wp[4]));
00141                 wp[21] = S(1, (u_long)(wp[18]^wp[13]^wp[7]^wp[5]));
00142                 wp[22] = S(1, (u_long)(wp[19]^wp[14]^wp[8]^wp[6]));
00143                 wp[23] = S(1, (u_long)(wp[20]^wp[15]^wp[9]^wp[7]));
00144                 wp += 8;
00145                 t--;
00146         } while (t > 0);
00147         
00148         A = h[0];
00149         B = h[1];
00150         C = h[2];
00151         D = h[3];
00152         E = h[4];
00153         
00154         t = 0;
00155         while (t<20) {
00156                 temp = S(5,A) + E + w[t++];
00157                 temp += (unsigned long)0x5a827999L + ((B&C)|(D&~B));
00158                 E = D; D = C; C = S(30,B); B = A; A = temp;
00159         }
00160         while (t<40) {
00161                 temp = S(5,A) + E + w[t++];
00162                 temp += (unsigned long)0x6ed9eba1L + (B^C^D);
00163                 E = D; D = C; C = S(30,B); B = A; A = temp;
00164         }
00165         while (t<60) {
00166                 temp = S(5,A) + E + w[t++];
00167                 temp += (unsigned long)0x8f1bbcdcL + ((B&C)|(B&D)|(C&D));
00168                 E = D; D = C; C = S(30,B); B = A; A = temp;
00169         }
00170         while (t<80) {
00171                 temp = S(5,A) + E + w[t++];
00172                 temp += (unsigned long)0xca62c1d6L + (B^C^D);
00173                 E = D; D = C; C = S(30,B); B = A; A = temp;
00174         }
00175         h[0] = MASK&(h[0] + A);
00176         h[1] = MASK&(h[1] + B);
00177         h[2] = MASK&(h[2] + C);
00178         h[3] = MASK&(h[3] + D);
00179         h[4] = MASK&(h[4] + E);
00180 }

00182 #define CHARSTOLONG(wp,s,i) {*wp++ = (u_long)((((u_long)(s[i])&0xff)<<24)|(((u_long)(s[i+1])&0xff)<<16)|(((u_long)(s[i+2])&0xff)<<8)|(u_long)(s[i+3]&0xff));}

00189         nbits = 0;

00191         mdContext->h[1] = (unsigned long)0xefcdab89L;
00192         mdContext->h[2] = (unsigned long)0x98badcfeL;
00193         mdContext->h[3] = (unsigned long)0x10325476L;

00199 void
00200 shsUpdate(mdContext, s, n)
00201   SHS_CTX *mdContext;
00202   unsigned char *s;
00203   unsigned int n;
00204 {
00205         register unsigned long *wp;
00206         long nn = n;
00207         long i;
00208         
00209         w = mdContext->w;
00210         h = mdContext->h;
00211         mdContext->totalLength += n;
00212         
00213         nbits = 0;
00214         n = n/(u_long)64;
00215         wp = w;
00216         
00217         while(n>0){
00218                 CHARSTOLONG(wp,s,0);
00219                 CHARSTOLONG(wp,s,4);
00220                 CHARSTOLONG(wp,s,8);
00221                 CHARSTOLONG(wp,s,12);
00222                 CHARSTOLONG(wp,s,16);
00223                 CHARSTOLONG(wp,s,20);
00224                 CHARSTOLONG(wp,s,24);
00225                 CHARSTOLONG(wp,s,28);
00226                 CHARSTOLONG(wp,s,32);
00227                 CHARSTOLONG(wp,s,36);
00228                 CHARSTOLONG(wp,s,40);
00229                 CHARSTOLONG(wp,s,44);
00230                 CHARSTOLONG(wp,s,48);
00231                 CHARSTOLONG(wp,s,52);
00232                 CHARSTOLONG(wp,s,56);
00233                 CHARSTOLONG(wp,s,60);
00234                 n--;
00235                 wp = w;
00236                 s = (s + 64);
00237                 shs1();
00238         }
00239         i=nn%64;
00240         while(i>3) {
00241                 CHARSTOLONG(wp,s,0);
00242                 s = (s + 4);
00243                 nbits += (u_long)32;
00244                 i -= 4;
00245         }
00246         while (i) {
00247                 opack((unsigned char)*s++);
00248                 i--;
00249         }
00250 }

00252 void
00253 shsFinal(mdContext)
00254   SHS_CTX *mdContext;
00255 {
00256         long nn = mdContext->totalLength;
00257         w = mdContext->w;
00258         h = mdContext->h;
00259         
00260         opack(128);
00261         while(nbits != 448)opack(0);
00262         packl((unsigned long)(nn>>29));
00263         packl((unsigned long)(nn<<3));
00264         
00265         /* if(nbits != 0)
00266            handle_exception(CRITICAL,"shsFinal(): nbits != 0\n");*/
00267 }

00269 unsigned char *
00270 qshs(s, n)
00271   unsigned char *s;
00272   long n;
00273 {
00274         SHS_CTX *mdContext;
00275         static SHS_CTX mdC;
00276         static unsigned char ret[20];
00277         int i;
00278         
00279         mdContext = &mdC;
00280 
00281         shsInit(mdContext);
00282         shsUpdate(mdContext, s, n);
00283         shsFinal(mdContext);
00284         for (i=0; i<5; i++) {
00285                 ret[i*4] = (mdContext->h[i]>>24)&0xff;
00286                 ret[i*4+1] = (mdContext->h[i]>>16)&0xff;
00287                 ret[i*4+2] = (mdContext->h[i]>>8)&0xff;
00288                 ret[i*4+3] = (mdContext->h[i])&0xff;
00289         }
00290         
00291         return ret;
00292 }

00296 unsigned long *
00297 fShsDigest(in)
00298   FILE *in;
00299 {
00300         SHS_CTX *mdContext;
00301         SHS_CTX mdC;
00302         unsigned char buffer[1024];
00303         long length, total;
00304 
00305         mdContext = &mdC;
00306         
00307         bzero(buffer, 1024);
00308 
00309         total = 0;
00310         shsInit(mdContext);
00311         while ((length = fread(buffer, 1, 1024, in)) != 0) {
00312                 total += length;
00313                 shsUpdate(mdContext, buffer, length);
00314         }
00315         shsFinal(mdContext);
00316 
00317         return mdContext->h;
00318 }
